# PCI Utilities Windows 11 Edition (PCIEDIT was updated to work in Windows11 (tested with 21H2)
1)Download windows gebugger from the links below (or u can just download the file from here)
2)Windows gebugger folder Add it to PATH
3)RUN gpedit.msc and add yourself rights to RUN as SYSTEM
4)Enable DEBUG in BCDEDIT (bcdedit /debug)
5)Reboot your system( I do recommend for the previous operation BOOTICE(https://www.majorgeeks.com/files/details/bootice_64_bit.html)
It makes it supereasy to change any boot arguments and many more! !!!
I HIGHLY RECOMMEND ALSO add argument DisplayAdvancedOptions TRUE in BOOTICE to your winodws bcd
So You will be able to easy access to safemode and other!
6)https://github.com/nonamebard/bettercamp_w11 download code and copy this folder to C:\ directory
7)find file called find_PCI_registers.bat in folder which You previously copied from the bettercamp_w11 repository and RUN it with Admin prevs
8)U will see the list of devices similar to my:

